2. Shorts price after discount: $35 * (1 - 0.3) = \boxed{24.50}
3. Total cost of the outfit after the discount: \boxed{17.50} + \boxed{24.50} = \boxed{42.00}
4. Money left after the purchase: $50 - \boxed{42.00} = \boxed{8.00}

Thus, we can conclude that \boxed{$8.00} will be the amount of money Joe will have left after the purchase of the outfit at the clothing store.

